name: "Change The System" #J4TMLA - White/Black
description:
On February 26, 2012 he lost his life.
On July 13, 2013 he lost his innocence.
We all feel the pain of Trayvon Martin’s absence. Now, we must all do our part to help prevent such a tragedy from ever recurring.
*****************
OUR LAWS NEED CHANGING. OUR LAW ENFORCEMENT NEEDS TRAINING. But more importantly our young people need hope. Our young people need to be reminded that they have the power to change the world and its views.
*****************
That is why for every “Change the System” shirt sold we are donating $2 to the Watts/Willowbrook and Los Angeles area Boys and Girls Clubs. Boys and Girls Club are leaders in bringing hope to our youth, and now you can too. SAVE OUR FUTURE 
*****************
